# Style Guide: Background Paths Aesthetic

This style guide defines the visual language for a minimal, elegant info website inspired by the Background Paths hero component. The aesthetic emphasizes clean neutrals, subtle gradients, refined typography, and smooth animations.

---

## Color Palette

Use a strictly neutral palette with subtle opacity variations for depth.

### Light Mode
```
Background:       white / #ffffff
Foreground:       neutral-900 / #171717
Muted:            neutral-700 / #404040 (80% opacity for secondary text)
Border:           black/10 (10% black opacity)
Surface:          white/95 (frosted glass effect)
```

### Dark Mode
```
Background:       neutral-950 / #0a0a0a
Foreground:       white / #ffffff
Muted:            white/80 (80% white opacity for secondary text)
Border:           white/10 (10% white opacity)
Surface:          black/95 (frosted glass effect)
```

### Tailwind Classes
```css
/* Backgrounds */
bg-white dark:bg-neutral-950

/* Text - Primary */
text-neutral-900 dark:text-white

/* Text - Secondary/Muted */
text-neutral-700/80 dark:text-white/80

/* Borders */
border-black/10 dark:border-white/10

/* Surfaces with glassmorphism */
bg-white/95 dark:bg-black/95 backdrop-blur-md
```

---

## Typography

### Font Stack
Use a geometric sans-serif system. Recommended: **Inter** or **Geist Sans**.

```tsx
// next.config or layout.tsx
import { Inter } from 'next/font/google'
const inter = Inter({ subsets: ['latin'] })
```

### Scale & Weights

| Element | Size | Weight | Tracking | Classes |
|---------|------|--------|----------|---------|
| Hero Title | 5xl-8xl | Bold (700) | Tighter | `text-5xl sm:text-7xl md:text-8xl font-bold tracking-tighter` |
| Page Title (h1) | 4xl-5xl | Bold (700) | Tighter | `text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tighter` |
| Section Title (h2) | 2xl-3xl | Semibold (600) | Tight | `text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight` |
| Subsection (h3) | xl-2xl | Semibold (600) | Tight | `text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight` |
| Body Large | lg | Normal (400) | Normal | `text-lg leading-relaxed` |
| Body | base | Normal (400) | Normal | `text-base leading-relaxed` |
| Small/Caption | sm | Medium (500) | Normal | `text-sm text-neutral-700/80 dark:text-white/80` |

### Gradient Text (Hero Only)
Use gradient text sparingly for hero titles only:

```tsx
<span className="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-neutral-900 to-neutral-700/80 dark:from-white dark:to-white/80">
  Your Title
</span>
```

---

## Buttons

### Primary Button
Frosted glass effect with subtle gradient border wrapper.

```tsx
<div className="inline-block group relative bg-gradient-to-b from-black/10 to-white/10 dark:from-white/10 dark:to-black/10 p-px rounded-2xl backdrop-blur-lg overflow-hidden shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-300">
  <button className="rounded-[1.15rem] px-8 py-4 text-base font-semibold backdrop-blur-md bg-white/95 hover:bg-white/100 dark:bg-black/95 dark:hover:bg-black/100 text-black dark:text-white transition-all duration-300 group-hover:-translate-y-0.5 border border-black/10 dark:border-white/10 hover:shadow-md dark:hover:shadow-neutral-800/50">
    <span className="opacity-90 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity">Button Text</span>
    <span className="ml-3 opacity-70 group-hover:opacity-100 group-hover:translate-x-1.5 transition-all duration-300">→</span>
  </button>
</div>
```

### Secondary Button (Ghost)
Minimal, transparent with border.

```tsx
<button className="px-6 py-3 text-sm font-medium rounded-xl border border-black/10 dark:border-white/10 text-neutral-900 dark:text-white hover:bg-black/5 dark:hover:bg-white/5 transition-all duration-200">
  Secondary Action
</button>
```

### Text Link Button
```tsx
<button className="text-sm font-medium text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-900 dark:hover:text-white transition-colors duration-200 underline-offset-4 hover:underline">
  Learn more
</button>
```

---

## Cards

### Standard Card
```tsx
<div className="group relative bg-gradient-to-b from-black/5 to-transparent dark:from-white/5 dark:to-transparent p-px rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
  <div className="rounded-[calc(1rem-1px)] p-6 bg-white/80 dark:bg-neutral-950/80 backdrop-blur-sm border border-black/5 dark:border-white/5">
    <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
      Card Title
    </h3>
    <p className="text-neutral-700/80 dark:text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
      Card description text goes here with relaxed line height for readability.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Elevated Card (Interactive)
```tsx
<div className="group relative bg-gradient-to-b from-black/10 to-white/10 dark:from-white/10 dark:to-black/10 p-px rounded-2xl backdrop-blur-lg overflow-hidden shadow-lg hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300">
  <div className="rounded-[calc(1rem-1px)] p-6 bg-white/95 dark:bg-black/95 backdrop-blur-md group-hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-transform duration-300">
    <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
      Interactive Card
    </h3>
    <p className="text-neutral-700/80 dark:text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
      This card lifts on hover with a subtle shadow increase.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Feature Card with Icon
```tsx
<div className="p-6 rounded-2xl border border-black/10 dark:border-white/10 bg-white/50 dark:bg-white/5 backdrop-blur-sm">
  <div className="w-10 h-10 rounded-xl bg-neutral-900 dark:bg-white flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
    <IconComponent className="w-5 h-5 text-white dark:text-neutral-900" />
  </div>
  <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold tracking-tight text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
    Feature Title
  </h3>
  <p className="text-sm text-neutral-700/80 dark:text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
    Feature description with smaller text for density.
  </p>
</div>
```

